title: San Thi Dar Restaurant
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Previously all-veg and at front of Archaeological Museum; moved to this location on the main road (no turns required). Added meat to its menu, but still offers many vegetable dishes. Like most places in Myanmar, you'll need to explain this in Burmese or point to it written down, though the owner's son speaks English and is sometimes present. Large portions. Try the shan tofu.
streetAddress: south of Old Bagan, Main Road, Myingabar Village
